@node ISO Size and Contents
@appendix ISO Size and Contents

@cindex ISO size
@cindex image size
@cindex userspace payload
@cindex boot media overhead

This appendix explains why the VibeOS ISO is large, what is actually taking up
space inside it, and how much of that size belongs to VibeOS itself rather than
to bundled third-party software and bootloader payloads.

The short version is simple: the kernel is small, but the shipped image is not
trying to be a tiny bootstrap environment.  Software installation is still
awkward, so the current policy is to ship a broad userland up front and defer
size reduction until the post-boot install story is much better.

The figures below were measured from the current build artifacts in
@file{build/} on 2026-04-23.

